Virtual Particles & Quantum Vacuum 
530.13 — Quantum field theory (QFT)
In short, the ground state has structure and energy, it's the 
dynamic potential enabling particle physics and possibly 
spacetime itself.

The ground state is not empty ... it is the active relational 
field from which excitations and geometry arise.

Key Equations 

1. Time–energy relation
   ΔE Δt ≳ ħ/2

   DeltaE * DeltaT >= hbar/2
   -> Minimal condition for virtual excitations (short-lived
      energy fluctuations allowed by quantum uncertainty).

2. Scalar Feynman propagator
   D_F(x - y) = ∫ d^4k / (2π)^4 * [ i / (k^2 - m^2 + iε) ] * e^{-ik·(x - y)}

   D_F(x - y) =
      ∫ d^4k / (2*pi)^4 *
        [ i / (k^2 - m^2 + i*epsilon) ] *
        exp( -i * k · (x - y) )

   -> Green's function for a scalar field: amplitude for a
      disturbance at x to appear at y.

3. Virtual exchange factor
   1 / (q^2 - m^2 + iε)

   1 / ( q^2 - m^2 + i*epsilon )

   -> Internal-line factor in diagrams: virtual propagator
      carrying momentum q

4. Vacuum two-point function
   ⟨0 | T φ(x) φ(y) | 0⟩ = D_F(x - y) ≠ 0

   <0 | T phi(x) phi(y) | 0> = D_F(x - y) != 0

   -> Vacuum is not empty; correlations exist even with no
      particles.

5. Zero-point energy
   E_0 = (1/2) Σ_k ħ ω_k

   E_0 = (1/2) * Sum_k ( hbar * omega_k )

   -> Each mode contributes (1/2) hbar * omega.
      Origin of vacuum energy

6. Field operator expansion
   φ(x) = ∫ d^3k / [ (2π)^3 √(2ω_k) ] *
          ( a_k e^{-ik·x} + a_k† e^{ik·x} )

   phi(x) =
      ∫ d^3k / [ (2*pi)^3 * sqrt(2*omega_k) ] *
        ( a_k * exp(-i*k·x) + a_k^dagger * exp(i*k·x) )

   -> Creation and annihilation operators build the field
      from modes.

7. One-loop vacuum bubble
   i ∫ d^4k / (2π)^4 * [ 1 / (k^2 - m^2 + iε) ]

   i * ∫ d^4k / (2*pi)^4 *
        [ 1 / (k^2 - m^2 + i*epsilon) ]

   -> Closed loop with no external legs: pure vacuum
      fluctuation.

8. Feynman rules (internal lines)
   Scalar:  i / (p^2 - m^2 + iε)
   Fermion: i ( /p + m ) / (p^2 - m^2 + iε)

   Scalar:
      i / ( p^2 - m^2 + i*epsilon )
   Fermion:
      i * ( p_slash + m ) / ( p^2 - m^2 + i*epsilon )

   -> Propagators inserted for internal lines.

9. Mass renormalization counterterm
   m_0^2 = m_r^2 + δm^2
   δm^2 ∝ ∫^Λ d^4k / (k^2 - m^2)

   m_0^2 = m_r^2 + delta_m^2
   delta_m^2 ∝ ∫^Lambda d^4k / ( k^2 - m^2 )

   -> Bare mass = renormalized mass + divergent correction.

10. Vacuum energy density (cutoff)
    ρ_vac ≈ Λ^4 / (16π^2)

    rho_vac ≈ Lambda^4 / (16*pi^2)

    -> Quartic divergence from summing zero-point modes up
       to cutoff Lambda.

11. Dyson series (S-matrix)
    S = T exp( -i ∫ H_int(t) dt )

    S = T exp( -i ∫ H_int(t) dt )

    -> Time-ordered exponential generating all perturbative
       interactions.

12. Wick’s theorem
    T(φ_1 ... φ_n) = :N(...): + all contractions

    T( phi1 ... phin ) =
       : N( ... ) :  +  all contractions

    -> Converts time-ordered products into normal-ordered
       ones plus propagators.
